https://indianexpress.com/article/business/banking-and-finance/rbi-forms-committee-for-ethical-enablement-of-ai-in-financial-sector-9746414/,https://indianexpress.com/article/business/banking-and-finance/rbi-forms-committee-for-ethical-enablement-of-ai-in-financial-sector-9746414/lite/,RBI forms committee for ethical enablement of AI in financial sector,20241226T231500Z,https://images.indianexpress.com/2024/12/RBI_e2d2c1.jpg,indianexpress.com,English,India,XLF,Financial,financial sector,"skip to content Advertisement Premium RBI forms committee for ethical enablement of AI in financial sector The committee, to be headed by Pushpak Bhattacharyya, professor (Department of Computer Science and Engineering), IIT Bombay, will recommend a robust, comprehensive, and adaptable AI framework for the financial sector. By: ENS Economic Bureau Mumbai | Updated: December 27, 2024 10:48 PM IST 2 min read Whatsapp twitter Facebook Reddit PRINT The committee will submit its report within six months from the date of its first meeting, the RBI said. The Reserve Bank of India (RBI) has constituted an eight-member committee of experts to develop a framework for responsible and ethical enablement of artificial intelligence (FREE-AI) in the financial sector. The committee, to be headed by Pushpak Bhattacharyya, professor (Department of Computer Science and Engineering), IIT Bombay, will recommend a robust, comprehensive, and adaptable AI framework for the financial sector. The committee will assess the current level of adoption of AI in financial services, globally and in India, and review regulatory and supervisory approaches on AI with focus on the financial sector globally. Story continues below this ad As part of the terms of reference, the committee will identify potential risks associated with AI, if any and recommend an evaluation, mitigation and monitoring framework and consequent compliance requirements for financial institutions, including banks, non-bank finance companies (NBFCs), fintechs and payment system operators (PSOs). It will also recommend a framework including governance aspects for responsible, ethical adoption of AI models / applications in the domestic financial sector, the RBI said. Besides Bhattacharyya, the other members of the committee are Debjani Ghosh, independent director, Reserve Bank Innovation Hub; Balaraman Ravindran, professor and head (Wadhwani School of Data Science and AI), IIT Madras; Abhishek Singh, additional secretary, Ministry of Electronics and Information Technology; Rahul Matthan, partner, Trilegal; Anjani Rathor, group head and chief digital experience officer, HDFC Bank ; Sree Hari Nagaralu, head of security AI research, Microsoft India (R&D); and Suvendu Pati, CGM, FinTech Department, RBI. The committee will submit its report within six months from the date of its first meeting, the RBI said. Expand ¬© The Indian Express Pvt Ltd Tags: RBI Latest Comment Post Comment Read Comments Advertisement Man at the wheel: Umar Nabi, doctor who ‚Äòmotivated white-collar group‚Äô India 3 hr ago Police suspect that Dr Umar Nabi Bhat was the leader of a terror module of doctors, including Dr Muzammil Ahmad Ganai and Dr Adeel Majeed Rather, who were involved in the recent Red Fort explosion. Bhat's family was taken away for questioning, while Ganai's family was shocked to learn of his involvement. View all shorts Live Blog Bihar Election 2025 Exit Polls LIVE Updates: NDA likely to retain power in Bihar, predict 9 exit polls 10 hours ago CAT 2025 Admit Card LIVE Updates: IIM Kozhikode to release hall ticket on Wednesday 13 hours ago Top News Headlines of November 11, 2025 | Singaporean moneylender who fatally stabbed debtor pleads guilty at the age of 80 after 33 years on the run 6 hours ago Bihar Election 2025 LIVE Updates: State sees highest-ever turnout since 1951 as 66.91% voters cast their ballots 10 hours ago Advertisement PHOTOS In Pics: From Concept Supercars to Electric SUVs ‚Äì Innovation at Bharat Mobilit